# Task T-014@20260416T181925Z: Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries.

## Acceptance Criteria

- `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, MusDr/MusPy for symbolic metrics, librosa for audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty, madmom for beat/tempo cross-check<br/>- documented pass bands from the research: IOI CoV 0.04–0.12, velocity σ 12–22, DNVR 0.25–0.7, pitch H1 2.3–3.0, GS 0.6–0.9, tempo ρ₁ 0.7–0.95, LZ76 0.4–0.7, ≥1 novelty peak per phrase, ≥100 ms silence at phrase boundaries<br/>- tests run metrics on rule-disabled flat-line control (should fail pass bands) and full-stack render (should pass)

**Tier:** T1

## Instructions

1. Read the failing test or bug report to understand the core issue.
2. Make the minimal code change required to fix the problem.
3. Run the relevant tests to confirm the fix and ensure no regressions were introduced.
4. Commit the change with a clear commit message: `fix(scope): summary [T-014@20260416T181925Z]`

